      "instructions": "Preheat oven to 325F.Lightly grease a 8x8 pan with cooking spray and set aside.Combine melted coconut oil, sugar, Dutch-processed Cocoa Powder, and salt . It will look gritty but it will become smooth once the other ingredients are added.Stir in the vanilla extract. Add eggs one at a time.When the batter looks thick, shiny, and well blended, add all-purpose flour and stir until you cannot see it any longer. Gently fold in chopped walnuts. Spread brownie mix evenly in the greased pan.In a medium saucepan, over medium heat add raspberry jam with preserves. Heat until jam is smooth and liquid. Pour raspberry jam over brownie mixture in a haphazard pattern.Bake for 20-25 minutes {I did 25} or until a toothpick inserted into the center emerges slightly moist with batter. Let cool completely and serve.",
