      "instructions": "Preheat oven to 325F.Place ramekins in a baking dish (a 9x13 was the perfect size for us). Fill the baking pan with water so it reaches halfway up the sides of the ramekins.Distribute diced mango evenly among the ramekins.In a 2 cup liquid measuring cup (the spout here makes later steps easier), whisk together egg yolks and sugar.In a small saucepan, mix vanilla and cream. Heat over medium heat until the cream just begins to smoke and a film appears over the top. (You do not want the cream to boil.)Slowly pour the cream into the egg mixture, whisking constantly.Pour custard into ramekins to cover the mango.Bake until the custards have set, 35 minutes.Transfer custards to a wire rack to cool, then refrigerate, uncovered, until well cooled (3-4 hours or overnight works well).Just before serving the crème brulee, sprinkle the top of each with roughly 1 tsp of sugar.Caramelize the sugar with a blow torch, or preheat your broiler and broil for 2-3 minutes.",
